About this property

Barbarosa Formentera

Villa Barbarosa has an excellent location in the heart of the Sa Talaiassa forest nature reserve, surrounded by Mediterranean vegetation, which is accessed through a private unpaved road, being one of the areas with the most privacy and tranquility of Formentera


It stands out for its spectacular panoramic view of the sea, the Es Cap de Barbaria Lighthouse, and Es Vedr and Ibiza, offering the best sun and moonsets on the Island.

The interior consists of five rooms, two of them en suite, one of them with hydromassage, four have a double bed and one of them is single, all of them have air conditioning, TV, wardrobe, and mirror. Both bathrooms have double sinks.

The prices and rates shown are based on 6 people per night. For more or less number of people contact the owner for prices, conditions and availability.

The dining room of 45 m2 and the fully equipped kitchen connect with the solarium on the top floor, and with the main terrace, from where you can access a Chill Out with a platform, in which to contemplate the impressive views lying on a Balinese bed, and also to the garden, where the barbecue and the pool are located.

It has wi-fi, laundry and private parking.


Our prices include all fees. No hidden fees.

About the neighborhood

Formentera

Located in Formentera, this villa is in a rural area and on the waterfront. Can Blai Roman Castle and La Mola Lighthouse are local landmarks, and some of the area's activities can be experienced at La Mola Market and La Savina Port. Be sure to check out the area's animals with activities such as game walks and birdwatching.
